  "instruction": "Create a small tabs demo in VS Code at /home/user/Desktop/tabs_switcher_basic. Create index.html, styles.css, app.js, and manifest.json. Build a page with main#app, section#hero, nav#tab-nav containing exactly 3 button.tab-trigger elements with data-tab values overview, timeline, and assets, and section#tab-panels containing exactly 3 article.tab-panel elements matching those ids. One tab and one panel should start with the class is-active. In app.js, wire click handlers so clicking a tab updates the active trigger and panel. In manifest.json, set project to tabs-switcher-basic, theme to clay, and version to 1.0. Save all files.",
